, but differ in having larger epigynal wings (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF4FFB0FF2B3FACB61C9583" box="[232,297,2021,2044]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
