<bibRefCitation id="EF856F99FFF4FFB0FE953FACB55C9583" author="Rakov &amp; Logunov" box="[342,617,2021,2044]" firstAuthor="Rakov" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" pagination="67 - 104" refId="ref2699" refString="Rakov S. T., Logunov D. V. 1997. A critical review of the genus Heliophanus C. L. Koch, 1833, of Middle Asia and the Caucasus (Aranei: Salticidae). Arthropoda Selecta 5 (3 / 4): 67 - 104." type="journal article" year="1997">Rakov &amp; Logunov, 1997</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 81) and markedly smaller spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF4FFB0FDCC304FB5609A62" box="[527,597,2054,2077]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF856F99FFF4FFB0FD4F304FB4D99499" author="Rakov S. T. &amp; Logunov D. V." box="[652,1004,1743,2077]" firstAuthor="Rakov" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" pagination="67 - 104" refId="ref2699" refString="Rakov S. T., Logunov D. V. 1997. A critical review of the genus Heliophanus C. L. Koch, 1833, of Middle Asia and the Caucasus (Aranei: Salticidae). Arthropoda Selecta 5 (3 / 4): 67 - 104." type="journal article" year="1997">Rakov &amp; Logunov, 1997</bibRefCitation>
: figs 82-83). For the diagnosis of the male, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF856F99FFF4FFB0FC6A3EB9B36E9578" author="Logunov" box="[937,1115,1776,1799]" firstAuthor="Logunov" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" pagination="899 - 919" refId="ref2442" refString="Logunov D. V. 2009. New and poorly known species of Salticidae (Araneae) from Turkey and Iran. Contributions to Natural History 12: 899 - 919." type="journal article" year="2009">Logunov (2009)</bibRefCitation>
