<subSubSection id="C30E41E3FFF4FFB6FCFC3F69B60F91A6" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAB1268FFF4FFB0FCFC3F69B4F89548" blockId="2.[831,1437,1824,2077]" box="[831,973,1824,1847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B960CE7AFFF4FFB0FCFC3F69B4F89548" bold="true" box="[831,973,1824,1847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Description:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB1268FFF4FFB0FCFC3F08B35F9506" blockId="2.[831,1437,1824,2077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B960CE7AFFF4FFB0FCFC3F08B4429527" box="[831,887,1857,1880]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Male</emphasis>
: See 
<bibRefCitation id="EF856F99FFF4FFB0FC0F3F08B3B89527" author="Logunov" box="[972,1165,1857,1880]" firstAuthor="Logunov" pageId="2" pageNumber="22" pagination="899 - 919" refId="ref2442" refString="Logunov D. V. 2009. New and poorly known species of Salticidae (Araneae) from Turkey and Iran. Contributions to Natural History 12: 899 - 919." type="journal article" year="2009">Logunov (2009)</bibRefCitation>
. The studied male is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF4FFB0FC0F3F2BB3139506" box="[972,1062,1890,1913]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Figs 1-5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF4FFB0FBF13F2BB3509506" box="[1074,1125,1890,1913]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">9-10</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB1268FFF4FFB6FCFC3FCBB60F91A6" blockId="2.[831,1437,1824,2077]" lastBlockId="4.[151,757,258,985]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="24" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B960CE7AFFF4FFB0FCFC3FCBB4BA95E6" box="[831,911,1922,1945]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="22">Female</emphasis>
: Carapace 1.70 long, 1.30 wide, 0.75 high at PLE. Ocular area 0.75 long, 1.05 wide anteriorly and 1.05 wide posteriorly. Diameter of AME 0.35. Abdomen 2.70 long, 1.90 wide. Cheliceral length 0.50. Clypeal height 0.05. Length of leg segments: I 2.65 (0.80 + 0.50 + 0.55 + 0.45 + 0.35); II 2.45 (0.80 + 0.40 + 0.50 + 0.45 + 0.30); III 3.00 (0.90 + 0.50 + 0.55 + 0.65 + 0.40); IV 3.85 (1.15 + 0.55 + 0.85 + 0.80 + 0.50). Leg spination: I: Fm d 1-1-1; Tb pr 0-1, v 2-0; Mt v 2-2 ap. II: Fm d 1-1-1; Tb pr 0-1, v 1-0; Mt v 2-2 ap. III: Fm d 1-1-2; Tb pr and rt 0-1, v 2 ap; Mt pr 2 ap, rt 2 ap, v 2 ap. IV: Fm d 1-1-1; Tb pr and rt 1-1, v 2 ap; Mt pr and rt 1-2 ap, v 1-0-2 ap. Coloration: Carapace dark brown, almost black, shiny, covered with sparse white scales (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF2FFB6FEF23A6BB6B69046" box="[305,387,546,569]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Sternum dark brown (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF2FFB6FD503A6BB5D29046" box="[659,743,546,569]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Labium and endites brown, with pale apexes. Chelicerae dark brown. Clypeus and cheeks brown, covered with short white hairs. Abdomen brown ventrally, covered with white scales; dorsum dark brown, covered with white and iridescent scales (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF2FFB6FE0E3A8BB52890A6" box="[461,541,706,729]" captionStart="Figs 9-12" captionStartId="3.[151,192,851,872]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,259,809]" captionTargetId="figure-6@3.[151,1429,254,833]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 9-12. Habitus of Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (9-10) Male from Ilam Province, dorsal and ventral view. (11-12) Female, dorsal and ventral view. Scale bars 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743464" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743464/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Book-lung covers brown. Spinnerets dark brown. Palps yellow, covered with white hairs. Palpal coxa dark brown, palpal tibia covered with brown hairs. All legs yellow. Coxa IV dark brown retrolaterally. Fm I with four stridulatory hairs. Epigyne and spermathecae as in 
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF2FFB6FDD33B2BB5449106" box="[528,625,866,889]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Figs 6-8</figureCitation>
: copulatory openings hidden under C-shaped epigynal wings (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF2FFB6FF5C3BEBB7D691C6" box="[159,227,930,953]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), spermathecae small, with two short accessory glands (
<figureCitation id="132F0EEDFFF2FFB6FF283B8BB61991A6" box="[235,300,962,985]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="2.[151,192,1590,1611]" captionTargetBox="[172,1433,265,1540]" captionTargetId="figure-162@2.[151,1436,257,1564]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1-8. Heliophanus xerxesi Logunov, 2009. (1-2) Male palp, ventral and retrolateral view. (3-5) Male palpal femur, prolateral (3-4) and retrolateral (5) view. (6) Epigyne, ventral view. (7) Diagrammatic course of insemination ducts. (8) Vulva, dorsal view. (1-3, 5) Specimen from Markazi Province. (4, 6-8) Specimens from Ilam Province. Scale bars 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5743462" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5743462/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="24">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
